  stringCount: 5
  line1:
  - 'Welcome to the tutorial! If you''ve played <b>[Minesweeper]</b> before, you''ll
    find this easy to grasp.



'
  - 'As a treasure hunter, you must avoid traps and <b>[collect all the treasures]</b>
    to proceed to the next level.

'
  - 'The numbers written on the floor represent the sum of <b>[traps and treasures]</b>
    surrounding that number.


    Using this, you can distinguish between rocks
    hiding <b>[treasures or traps]</b> and those that are not.'
  - You can move by <b>[clicking on adjacent tiles]</b>. Give it a try and move around!
  line1Animation: []
  line2:
  - Just like you did now, by <b>[clicking a certain location]</b>, you can <b>[move
    to that spot]</b>.
  - 'Look around, and you''ll find rocks where it''s certain that <b>[treasures or
    traps are hidden]</b>.


    <b>[Right-click]</b> on such rocks to <b>[mark]</b>
    them.'
  line2Animation: []
  line3:
  - 'This way, you can differentiate the marked rocks for sure.


    Remember, you
    can only <b>[mark rocks that are accessible]</b>.'
  - 'Now, let''s clear some rocks. <b>[Left-click]</b> on a nearby rock to shovel
    it away.


    To clear a rock, you need to be <b>[right beside it]</b>.'
  line3Animation: []
  line4:
  - If you hit a trap, you'll take damage; if you find a treasure, you'll get an
    item.
  - Now, let's find all the treasures in the field and open the door to the next
    level.
  line4Animation: []
  line5:
  - The door to the next level is open! Hurry to the stairs and head down to the
    next floor."
  line5Animation: []
